## Grid Basics Review
Brief overview of fundamental grid concepts:
- `display: grid` - Creates a grid container
- Grid lines, tracks, and cells
- Grid columns and rows
- Explicit vs implicit grid

## Advanced Properties

### Grid Template Properties
- `grid-template-columns` - Define column sizes
- `grid-template-rows` - Define row sizes
- `grid-template-areas` - Create named grid areas
- `grid-template` - Shorthand property

#### grid-template-areas Example
`grid-template-areas` allows you to define named grid areas, making layouts more readable and maintainable.

**HTML:**
```html
<div class="container">
  <header>Header</header>
  <nav>Navigation</nav>
  <main>Main Content</main>
  <aside>Sidebar</aside>
  <footer>Footer</footer>
</div>
```

**CSS:**
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 3fr 1fr;
  grid-template-rows: auto 1fr auto;
  grid-template-areas:
    "header header header"
    "nav main aside"
    "footer footer footer";
  gap: 1rem;
  height: 100vh;
}

header {
  grid-area: header;
  background-color: #3498db;
  padding: 1rem;
}

nav {
  grid-area: nav;
  background-color: #2c3e50;
}

main {
  grid-area: main;
  background-color: #ecf0f1;
}

aside {
  grid-area: aside;
  background-color: #95a5a6;
}

footer {
  grid-area: footer;
  background-color: #34495e;
  padding: 1rem;
}
```

**Key Points:**
- Use string values with area names in `grid-template-areas`
- Each row represents a line of the grid (spaces between names)
- Use the `grid-area` property to assign items to named areas
- This creates a visual representation of your layout in the CSS

### Item Placement
- `grid-column` - Span columns
- `grid-row` - Span rows
- `grid-placement` - Shorthand property
- `grid-auto-flow` - Control auto-placement

### Alignment Properties
- `justify-items` - Horizontal alignment
- `align-items` - Vertical alignment
- `justify-content` - Distribute columns
- `align-content` - Distribute rows

### Gap Properties
- `grid-gap` / `gap` - Space between items
- `column-gap` - Space between columns
- `row-gap` - Space between rows

## Layout Patterns
Common CSS Grid patterns and use cases:
- Holy Grail Layout
- Card Grid Layouts
- Responsive Image Galleries
- Dashboard Layouts

## Responsive Design
- Using `auto-fit` and `auto-fill`
- `minmax()` function for flexible grids
- Media queries with grid
- Mobile-first approach

## Best Practices
- Use meaningful grid names
- Keep grid declarations readable
- Test across browsers
- Combine Grid with Flexbox appropriately
- Plan your layout before coding

